        "kind": "pull_request",
        "title": "fix: add timeout to scp spawn to prevent hanging in sandbox media staging",
        "body": "Related: #98468\n\n## What Problem This Solves\n\nFixes `scpFile()` spawning scp child process with no timeout, causing hung processes and Promise leaks.\n\n## Why This Change Was Made\n\nAdd 30-second `SCP_TIMEOUT_MS` with `SIGKILL` and Promise rejection. `settled` flag prevents double-resolution.\n\n## User Impact\n\nPrevents hung SCP operations from leaking resources during remote sandbox media staging.\n\n## Evidence\n\nRuntime verification (fix/scp-timeout, rebased on upstream/main 6495358f):\n\n```\nstage-sandbox-media.scp-remote-path.test.ts — Test Files 1 passed, Tests 5 passed\n✓ stageSandboxMedia scp remote paths > keeps only the tail of noisy scp stderr\n✓ stageSandboxMedia scp remote paths > rejects remote attachment filenames before spawning scp\n✓ stageSandboxMedia scp remote paths > rewrites remote iMessage attachment metadata\n... (5/5 ✓, Duration 4.45s)\n```\n\n[test] passed 1 Vitest shard. Timeout pattern follows `src/crestodian/probes.ts`.",
